x4freetext: Characteristics of the simultaneous measurements with
two detectors for 3 runs given in table 1 (p.217)
uranium target slowed down by a 2.8 cm thick 20*20 cm2
.The neutron spectrum was proportional to En**(-0.887)
below 41 eV   above 41 eV*  below 41 eV   above 41 eV
time of flight, flight path = 60.58 m.
.Two flight paths are used simultaneously forming an
angle of -9 and +9 degrees with the axis perpendicular
.Flight path A has 3 collimators, at the target room,
at the 30 m. Station and at the detector station at
60 m. The detector is a fission neutron detector.
.Flight path B has 2 collimators, at the target room,
and in the detector station at 60 m. The detector is
hollow cylinder with outer diam.38 cm, outer length
38 cm, inner diam.16 cm,inner length 16 cm.
.Sample in the middle of the cylinder.
.Each chamber is viewed by a 58 AVP photomultiplier,
via a pulse shape gamma discriminator pair-wise linked
to six two-input coincidence circuits giving a stop
signal to the time-of-flight analyzer via an `or` gate
.Electrodes 26 cm diameter 35 mm thick aluminium foils
.In aluminium box with 0.6 mm thick windows.
.Discriminated against alpha particles up to 20 MeV
.For neutron flux measurements a bank of BF3-
counters placed 1 m behind the fission detectors
.Shielded against low energy background neutrons by
8 and 10 eV for the lower energy run.
.The Shore data are normalized to a 2200 m/sec
.Higher energy runs have been normalized via the
.Corrected for background by black resonance technique.
.No correction for resolution and Doppler effects
SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
.Only fission detector data given. Neutron detector
.The three runs have been concatenated without overlap
